\begin{motivation}[Splits, not coefficients]
Linear models fit one hyperplane defined by a coefficient vector. Tree models partition the feature space into rectangular cells defined by a sequence of splits, with a constant prediction per cell. The two geometries fail in different ways.
\end{motivation}

